Subject: Add realistic multi-file multi-package Haskell tests
Message-Id: <ae14dd6b6e8c58a6-0-artemis@nixos-framework>

The existing Haskell tests only create single-file projects with trivial code like "f x = x" or "foo = 5". The original issue e9cbc4d1d87f6e7f specifically asks for "realistic" tests that "cover e.g. projects containing multiple packages."

Need to implement the stub tests added in tests/haskell-tests.el:
- warbo-test-haskell-multi-package-project (cabal.project with multiple packages)
- warbo-test-haskell-stack-project (stack.yaml based projects)
- warbo-test-haskell-cross-module-references (multiple .hs files importing each other)
- warbo-test-haskell-external-dependencies (projects using text, aeson, etc.)

These should test realistic scenarios:
- Multiple modules with imports between them
- Cross-package jump-to-definition and refactoring
- Real library dependencies from Hackage/Stackage
- Proper module hierarchies (e.g., MyProject.Lib.Utils)
- Verify HLS can handle complex project structures

The with-haskell-eglot-test macro may need extension to support multi-file/multi-package setup.
